selectMessageAndEvaluate: aBlock defaultValue: aSelector	"Subclass may override me to allow the user to choose one selector, chosen from the currently selected message's selector, as well as those of all messages sent by it, and evaluate aBlock on behalf of chosen selector.  If there is only one possible choice, simply make it; if there are multiple choices, put up a menu, and evaluate aBlock on behalf of the the chosen selector, doing nothing if the user declines to choose any"	aBlock value: aSelector